# Styling Guide

This project uses UnoCSS for styling. The main configuration is in [uno.config.ts](mdc:uno.config.ts).

## Key Features

### Color System
- Primary colors: primary-100 to primary-900
- Gray scale: gray-50 to gray-900
- Dark slate: darkslate-50 to darkslate-900

### Typography
- Font families: CabinetGrotesk and Satoshi
- Usage: `font-sans` class for default font

### Custom Shadows
- Regular shadow: `shadow-custom`
- Hover shadow: `shadow-custom-hover`

### Grid System
- Auto-fill rows: `grid-rows-auto-250`
- Responsive columns: `grid-cols-4-minmax`

## Best Practices
1. Use atomic classes directly in components
2. Follow the color system for consistency
3. Utilize predefined shadows for depth
4. Apply responsive design using built-in utilities

## Example Usage
```html
<div class="bg-primary-500 text-white p-4 shadow-custom hover:shadow-custom-hover">
  <h1 class="font-sans text-2xl">Title</h1>
</div>
```
